id: pmc-sz4m
title: Remove host-specific path from published docs
description: Fix pm-changelog package docs so published npm tarballs do not include host-specific absolute paths that trip downstream secret/static scans.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: docs,packaging,security
created_at: "2026-05-23T23:38:56.042Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T23:43:02.267Z"
author: codex-changelog-integration
severity: high
environment: pm-cli CI installing pm-changelog@2026.5.24-1
repro_steps: "Install pm-changelog@2026.5.24-1 into pm-cli and run pnpm security:scan; docs/development.md line 104 is flagged as an absolute home path."
resolution: "Removed the host-specific absolute local install path from docs/development.md, redacted the original literal from item history, bumped the package version to 2026.5.24-2, and verified release:check."
expected_result: Published package docs avoid host-specific absolute paths or omit development-only host-local examples.
actual_result: Published docs include a host-specific absolute home path in the local install example.
component: package-docs
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T23:38:56.042Z",codex-changelog-integration,"Duplicate check: searched 'absolute home path docs package'; no dedicated open item exists. GitHub issue unbraind/pm-changelog#5 records the external report from pm-cli CI run 26346422405."
  "2026-05-23T23:40:23.293Z",codex-changelog-integration,"Evidence: replaced docs/development.md host-specific install path with a package_root variable, bumped package to 2026.5.24-2, redacted the path from item history, rg no longer finds host-specific absolute path patterns in package docs/source, and npm run release:check passed."
  "2026-05-23T23:43:02.267Z",codex-changelog-integration,"Evidence update: generated CHANGELOG.md with pm-changelog after closing pmc-sz4m, hardened .github/workflows/release.yml with --allow-same-version for corrective releases, and npm run release:check passed again."
